did.unittitle: Central Washington University Office of the President, Administrative Records

physdesc.extent: 10 letter sized document cases and 1 half letter sized document case

did.abstract: The collection consists of strategic reports, salary equity surveys, educational exchange and consortium agreements, and correspondences created or received by the Office of the President at Central Washington University from 1979 to 2002.

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The Office of the President at Central Washington University originated with the appointment of a Principal for Washington State Normal School by the Board of Trustees in the fall of 1891. The title of Principal was changed to President in 1914 and continues in use today.

scopecontent.p: Along with other records, this collection contains planning notes, budget requests, reorganization reports, and educational agreement contracts from the departments of Academic Affairs, International Programs, Strategic Planning, and University Centers at Central Washington University.

odd.p: Central Washington University began as the Washington State Normal School in 1891. In 1937, the school was rechristened the Central Washington College of Education. In 1961, the school became Central Washington State College and, finally, in 1977, Central Washington University.

arrangement.p: Alphabetical by subject title of file and chronological within file.

accessrestrict.p: Open to the public for educational research.
